article.headline: Albany 76, MD Baltimore Co 61
article.story: CATONSVILLE, Md. (AP) -- Reserve Jon Iati scored a career-high 29 points and Albany beat Maryland-Baltimore County 76-61 on Sunday, clinching its first America East regular season title. Lucious Jordan added 13 points and Brent Wilson and Kirsten Zoellner had 11 each for the Great Danes (18-10, 13-3), who have won eight of 10. Albany, which joined the conference in 2001, will be the top seed in the America East tournament in Vestal, N.Y., from March 3-5. John Zito led UMBC (9-18, 5-11) with 16 points, and Jerrell Dinkins and Chris Pugh added 10 apiece. The Retrievers, who have lost a season-high four games, will be seeded eighth in the conference tournament. Albany outrebounded the Retrievers 40-25, but the difference maker was 5-foot-9 Iati, who entered the contest averaging six points per game. Iati scored 20 first-half points, helping the Great Danes to a 35-26 halftime lead. He finished with six 3-pointers, matching a career high. Albany was 6-for-12 from 3-point range in the first half, while UMBC shot only 9-for-25 from the field. Consecutive 3-pointers by Iati out of the right corner gave Albany a 21-12 lead with 9:54 remaining. The Retrievers responded with a 6-0 run featuring four points by Zito to get within 21-18. The Great Danes scored only once from the field in the opening 4:36 of the second half, but UMBC couldn't capitalize on the dry spell. The Retrievers used a right-wing 3-pointer by Jay Greene and a Zito layup to cut Albany's lead to 44-38 with 13:27 left in the game, but Jordan's 3 quickly restored the advantage to nine points.
